Sentencas: In this work, symmetric electrolyte-supported YSZ (yttria-stabilized zirconia) cells infiltrated with LSF (La0.8Sr0.2FeO3O3-delta) were prepared, characterized, and tested in the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR).
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: The fabrication procedure of the cells was optimized with respect to the formulation of the electrolyte and electrode slips.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: Aqueous solutions of nitrates were used for the LSF-YSZ electrodes, which were morphologically characterized prior and after infiltration.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: The effects of calcination temperature (between 700 and 1050 degrees C) and precursors load (between 10% and 50% w/w) on the ORR activity were investigated.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) experiments were performed between 650 and 750 degrees C, with air and varying the O-2 partial pressure from 5% to 100%.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: The minimum polarization resistance was measured after calcination at 750 degrees C, while LSF loads between 20% and 40% maximized the performance.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells

Sentencas: Equivalent circuit analysis of the EIS results suggested that the surface reactivity at the LSF/gas interface is rate-determining.
Titulo: Preparation, Characterization, and Kinetic Testing of Infiltrated LSF-YSZ Electrodes for Symmetric Solid Oxide Cells
